Michael J Marx













                    
                    The author, Michael J. Marx, EdD (Regent University) has been embedded in the propagation of ethical coaching for many years. He leads the Global Ethics Community of Practice for the International Coach Federation and serves on their Independent Review Board. He also serves as the president of its Christian Coaches Network International where he leads efforts to instill moral integrity among the members. Additionally, he teaches Ethics at the Professional Christian Coaching Institute. Dr. Marx holds the Professional Certified Coach credential (ICF), the Professional Certified Cristian Coach credential (CCNI) as well as being a Certified Professional Life Coach (PCCI). He teaches MBA-level International Business and International Finance for the Concordia University of Wisconsin (CUW) and enjoys skiing and dog sledding. He and his wife Joy live in the mountains of Northwest Colorado with a dozen Alaskan huskies and a golden retriever named Angel.
                

