Michael J. Clain

	Partner 
		
Michael focuses on the structuring, negotiation, and documentation of a variety of credit products, including broadly syndicated corporate loans, asset-based loans, cash flow loans, trade and supply-chain finance, the purchase and sale of individual loans and loan portfolios, and the workout of troubled assets. His clients include money-center and regional banks, foreign banks, investment funds and finance companies. Representative Transactions - Middle Market ABL$45 million senior secured revolving credit facility to an importer and distributor of chemicals and its European subsidiaries.$22.5 million secured revolving credit facility to a taxi medallion financing and servicing company.$9 million senior secured revolving credit facility to a sponsor-owned jewelry retailer.$11 million senior secured credit facility to finance the acquisition of a specialty transportation company by two private equity funds.$14 million senior secured credit facility to an importer and distributor of specialty apparel and footwear.$15 million senior secured credit facility to a sponsor-backed graphics and communications company.Representative Transactions - Middle Market Cash Flow$97 million unsecured line of credit to a large healthcare company.$45 million senior loan to a newly-formed subsidiary of a European conglomerate to finance the acquisition of a vineyard.$23 million senior term loan and revolving credit facility to a for-profit education institution owned by several financial sponsors.$18 million secured credit facility to a key supplier of a major car manufacturer.$15 million secured credit facility to a distributor of consumer electronics products.$15 million senior secured revolving credit facility to an auto parts manufacturer.Representative Transactions - Broadly Syndicated LoansRegularly serve as counsel to several large banks in connection with their participation in broadly syndicated corporate transactions.Counsel to an asset-based lender in connection with the purchase of a $25 million assignment in a $175 million senior secured revolving credit facility to a business development company.Counsel to a foreign bank in connection with the purchase of an $87.5 million participation in a $1 billion margin loan to a media holding company.AuthoredWhat is Bitcoin and How Do I take a Security Interest In It?, Windels Marx Financial Transactions Newsletter (June 27, 2016)Eight risks to manage when buying trade receivables, Trade Financing Matters (April 17, 2014)Supplier Networks and Factors - Not a Match made in Heaven, Trade Financing Matters (March 31, 2014)The New Face of Trade Finance: The Rise of Supply Chain Finance (SCF), Windels Marx Webinar (July 10, 2013)Ocean Fright: Financing Goods in Transit Covered by Sea Waybills, BNA Banking Report (October 23, 2012)When Importer Security Filing Rules Conflict With Accepted Trade Finance Practice, BNA Banking Report (December 20, 2011)Memberships & Professional AffiliationsAmerican Bar Association (Member of the Business Law and International Law Sections)Herman Goldman Foundation (Director)Pelham Civic Association (Director)Village of Pelham, New York (Former Mayor)RecognitionSuperLawyers New York Metro 2015 - BankingSuperLawyers New York Metro 2014 - Banking, International and Securities & Corporate Finance




 








