Print Bio

Joshua J. Marx
Associate
Biography
Joshua Marx is a business litigator who represents individuals, small businesses as well as large, national clients in high stakes, complex business disputes.  His cases have involved issues concerning real estate, construction, product liability, employment and trust and estates.
Mr. Marx handles all aspects of the civil litigation process at both the state and federal level, as well as private arbitration and mediation.  Mr. Marx has successfully tried cases in front of juries, argued dispositive motions and taken and defended numerous depositions.
Representative Matters:

Second chaired jury trial, successfully defending corporate client against claim of multi-million dollar real estate fraud.
Represented tire manufacturer in an appellate matter where the court set aside a multi-million default judgment.
Participated in a successful jury trial involving breach of lease and fraud for a restaurant in Orange County.
In a trust and estates litigation, convinced the court to set aside a will and trust on grounds of fraud and undue influence.



